   REVIEW &amp; OUTLOOK (Editorial) -- Asides:
   Sick Terrorism
</HL>
<DATE>
06/08/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A10
</SO>
<GV>
HEALTH AND HUMAN SERVICES (HHS)
</GV>
<LP>
   The federal government's top expert has determined that
animal-rights activists can be bad for your health. Health
and Human Services Secretary Louis Sullivan says their
often-violent threats to necessary animal research delay
cures for many serious diseases. He complained about "major
disruptions to science by so-called animal activists who are,
