$205.6 million in 1989. Easco had 13.9 million weighted
average shares outstanding in 1989.
   Danaher, a Washington maker of tools and transportation
products, has 1989 revenue of about $756 million. Danaher
said it had about 23.8 million fully diluted common shares
outstanding in 1989.
