<HL>
   Uruguayan Consumer Prices
</HL>
<DATE>
06/08/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A5A
</SO>
<CO>
   LATAM
</CO>
<LP>
   MONTEVIDEO, Uruguay -- Prices of consumer goods rose 5.6%
in May, boosting Uruguay's 12-month inflation rate to three
digits for the first time in nearly 16 years, the government
said.
   The May increase brought inflation in the past 12 months
to 103.5%. Prices rose 38% in the first five months of 1990.
The inflation rate for all 1989 was 89%.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The government of President Luis Lacalle, who was
inaugurated March 1, has said it will take steps to reduce
the budget deficit, considered to be the principal cause of
the rising inflation rate.
</TEXT>
